<bibRefCitation author="Emerit, M" journalOrPublisher="Faune Madagascar" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 215" refId="B25" refString="Emerit, M, 1974. Arachnides araignees Araneidae Gasteracanthinae. Faune Madagascar 38: 1 - 215" title="Arachnides araignees Araneidae Gasteracanthinae." volume="38" year="1974">Emerit 1974</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barrion, AT" journalOrPublisher="CAB International Wallingford, UK" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B4" refString="Barrion, AT, Litsinger, JA, 1995. Riceland Spiders of South and Southeast Asia. CAB International Wallingford, UK" title="Riceland Spiders of South and Southeast Asia." year="1995">Barrion and Litsinger 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dierkens, M" journalOrPublisher="Revue Arachnologique" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="63 - 81" refId="B21" refString="Dierkens, M, Charlat, S, 2011. Contribution a la connaissance des araignees des iles de la Societe (Polynesie francaise). Revue Arachnologique 17 (5): 63 - 81" title="Contribution a la connaissance des araignees des iles de la Societe (Polynesie francaise)." volume="17" year="2011">Dierkens and Charlat 2011</bibRefCitation>
). Currently, it is classified as a monotypic species (
<bibRefCitation author="World Spider Catalog" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity and Conservation" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" publicationUrl="http://wsc.nmbe.ch" refId="B97" refString="World Spider Catalog, 2020. World Spider Catalog. Version 21.0. Natural History Museum Bern. http://wsc.nmbe.ch" title="World Spider Catalog. Version 21.0. Natural History Museum Bern." url="http://wsc.nmbe.ch" year="2020">World Spider Catalog 2020</bibRefCitation>
). However, the results of species delimitation have demonstrated four distinct species in the 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. brevispina" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="brevispina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">T. brevispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lineage (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Ultrametric tree generated by BEAST from 675 bp of COI gene showing clusters of OTUs as suggested by morphological identification, and three molecular species delimitation algorithms, ABGD, bPTP, and GMYC. Nodal support values are labeled as MP Jackknife support / ML bootstrap values / Bayesian posterior probability. Gene tree from MP and ML analyses are available as Suppl. material 1 (Suppl. material 1: Figs S 3, S 4)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1032.62001.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/532437" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4</figureCitation>
